# Interactive Web Development Demos

A collection of interactive demonstrations for learning web development concepts. Each demo provides hands-on experience with different aspects of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

## Table of Contents
- [Demo Descriptions](#demo-descriptions)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Features](#features)
- [Contributing](#contributing)

## Demo Descriptions

### 1. HTML Elements Showcase
Demonstrates basic HTML elements and their properties.
- Add/remove different HTML elements
- Live preview of element appearance
- Real-time HTML code display
- Interactive element manipulation

### 2. CSS Position Properties Demo
Visualizes different CSS position properties:
- Static (default)
- Relative
- Absolute
- Fixed
- Sticky
- Interactive positioning with real-time updates

### 3. CSS Display Properties Demo
Shows various CSS display property behaviors:
- Block
- Inline
- Inline-block
- Flex
- Grid
- None
- Live examples with visual feedback

### 4. Box Sizing Demo
Demonstrates the CSS box model:
- Content-box vs Border-box
- Interactive width/padding/border controls
- Visual dimension calculations
- Real-time updates

### 5. CSS Grid Demo
Interactive grid layout demonstration:
- Grid template columns/rows
- Grid gaps
- Item alignment
- Real-time CSS code generation

### 6. Flexbox Demo
Comprehensive flexbox properties showcase:
- Flex direction
- Justify content
- Align items
- Flex wrap
- Interactive item controls

### 7. Media Queries Demo
Responsive design visualization:
- Breakpoint management
- Layout changes
- Visual width indicators
- Live CSS generation

### 8. JavaScript Selectors Demo
Interactive DOM selection methods:
- getElementById
- getElementsByClassName
- querySelector
- querySelectorAll
- Live element highlighting

### 9. DOM Explorer
Visual DOM structure demonstration:
- Tree view navigation
- Element properties
- DOM manipulation methods
- Real-time updates

### 10. Form with JSON Preview
Interactive form field demonstration:
- Various input types
- Real-time validation
- JSON data preview
- Submit prevention

## Installation

No installation required! These are standalone HTML files that can be run directly in any modern web browser.

1. Download the desired demo file
2. Open it in your web browser
3. Start experimenting!

